---
// Instagram carousel export — not linked from the site, screenshot each slide
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>Carousel: SQL vs NoSQL</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Atkinson+Hyperlegible:wght@400;700&family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,400;9..144,900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>

<!-- SLIDE 1: Cover -->
<div class="slide cover">
  <div class="slide-num">1/7</div>
  <div class="tag">DEVOPS</div>
  <h1>SQL vs NoSQL:<br/>What the Fuss<br/>Is About</h1>
  <p class="sub">Two ways to store data.<br/>Two very different bets.</p>
  <div class="brand">Lit Bulb Lab</div>
</div>

<!-- SLIDE 2: What's a database -->
<div class="slide dark-card">
  <div class="slide-num">2/7</div>
  <h2>First: what even is a database?</h2>
  <p class="highlight">A spreadsheet you can talk to with code.</p>
  <p>You store information in it, ask it questions, it answers fast — even with millions of rows.</p>
  <p>The interesting question is <em>how</em> you store that information. That's where SQL and NoSQL split.</p>
</div>

<!-- SLIDE 3: SQL -->
<div class="slide">
  <div class="slide-num">3/7</div>
  <h2>SQL: the spreadsheet model</h2>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-icon">📋</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Tables</strong>
        <p>Rows and columns, like a spreadsheet. Every row is one thing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-icon">🔒</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Fixed structure</strong>
        <p>Every row must have the same columns. Even if most are blank.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step">
      <span class="step-icon">🔍</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Powerful queries</strong>
        <p>"All orders over $50 from New York, sorted by date." One line.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SLIDE 4: NoSQL -->
<div class="slide accent-slide">
  <div class="slide-num light">4/7</div>
  <h2>NoSQL: the document pile</h2>
  <p class="big-text">Instead of rows, you store documents. Think: a sticky note with whatever you want on it.</p>
  <div class="code-block">
    <span class="code-line"><span class="key">"name"</span>: <span class="val">"Priya"</span>,</span>
    <span class="code-line"><span class="key">"email"</span>: <span class="val">"priya@example.com"</span>,</span>
    <span class="code-line"><span class="key">"theme"</span>: <span class="val">"dark"</span></span>
  </div>
  <p class="footnote">Each document can have completely different fields. No shared column list.</p>
</div>

<!-- SLIDE 5: Side by side -->
<div class="slide">
  <div class="slide-num">5/7</div>
  <h2>Side by side</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><td class="label">Structure</td><td class="a">Fixed columns</td><td class="b">Flexible docs</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="label">Best at</td><td class="a">Complex queries</td><td class="b">Fast lookups</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="label">Schema changes</td><td class="a">Painful</td><td class="b">Easy</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="label">Related data</td><td class="a">Joins</td><td class="b">Embed in doc</td></tr>
    <tr><td class="label">Consistency</td><td class="a">Strict</td><td class="b">Depends</td></tr>
  </table>
  <p class="caption">Neither is better. They solve different problems.</p>
</div>

<!-- SLIDE 6: When to use which -->
<div class="slide dark-card">
  <div class="slide-num">6/7</div>
  <h2>When to use which</h2>
  <div class="two-col">
    <div class="col">
      <p class="col-head sql-head">Reach for SQL when...</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Data is naturally relational</li>
        <li>You need complex questions across many rows</li>
        <li>Correctness matters more than speed</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
      <p class="col-head nosql-head">Reach for NoSQL when...</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Each item is mostly self-contained</li>
        <li>Your data shape changes a lot</li>
        <li>Optimising for read speed at scale</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SLIDE 7: CTA -->
<div class="slide cta-slide">
  <div class="slide-num light">7/7</div>
  <p class="teaser">Most apps could use either and be fine.</p>
  <h2>"Pick whichever one the tutorial<br/>you're following uses.<br/><em>Seriously.</em>"</h2>
  <div class="cta-foot">
    <p>Read the full explainer →</p>
    <p class="url">abedis.net/posts/sql-vs-nosql</p>
    <p class="handles">@litbulblab</p>
  </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --paper: #16130f;
    --paper-raised: #211c16;
    --ink: #f2ebdf;
    --ink-soft: #c3b9a8;
    --accent: #f47b4f;
    --accent-soft: #3a261c;
    --line: #322b22;
    --font-display: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    --font-body: 'Atkinson Hyperlegible', sans-serif;
  }

  body {
    background: #0a0806;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    color: var(--ink);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .slide {
    width: 1080px;
    height: 1080px;
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 80px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .slide-num {
    position: absolute;
    top: 60px;
    right: 80px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-weight: 900;
  }
  .slide-num.light { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); }

  /* SLIDE 1: Cover */
  .cover { justify-content: space-between; padding: 80px; }
  .tag {
    font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--accent); background: var(--accent-soft);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem; border-radius: 99px; width: fit-content;
  }
  .cover h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 4.8rem; font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.05; color: var(--ink); flex: 1; display: flex; align-items: center;
  }
  .cover .sub { font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .brand { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--ink); }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--ink);
  }
  p { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  em { color: var(--accent); font-style: normal; }

  /* SLIDE 2 */
  .dark-card { background: var(--paper-raised); }
  .highlight {
    background: var(--accent-soft); color: var(--accent) !important;
    border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.5rem !important; line-height: 1.4 !important;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* SLIDE 3: Steps */
  .steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.4rem; }
  .step {
    display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: flex-start;
    background: var(--paper-raised); border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .step-icon { font-size: 2rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .step strong { display: block; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .step p { margin: 0; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }

  /* SLIDE 4: Accent */
  .accent-slide { background: var(--accent); }
  .accent-slide h2 { color: #fff; font-size: 3.2rem; }
  .accent-slide .big-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9) !important; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.3rem !important; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .accent-slide .footnote { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65) !important; font-size: 1rem !important; font-style: italic; }

  .code-block {
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.25); border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .code-line { font-family: monospace; font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .key { color: #ffd699; }
  .val { color: #fff; }

  /* SLIDE 5: Table */
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  td { padding: 0.9rem 0.8rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); font-size: 1.1rem; }
  tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  td.label { color: var(--ink-soft); width: 30%; }
  td.a { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 700; width: 35%; }
  td.b { color: var(--ink); width: 35%; }
  .caption { font-size: 0.95rem !important; font-style: italic; }

  /* SLIDE 6: Two col */
  .two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
  .col-head { font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.1rem !important; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .sql-head { color: var(--accent) !important; }
  .nosql-head { color: var(--ink) !important; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  li { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.5; }

  /* SLIDE 7: CTA */
  .cta-slide { background: var(--paper-raised); justify-content: space-between; }
  .cta-slide .teaser { font-size: 1.1rem !important; color: var(--ink-soft) !important; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .cta-slide h2 { font-size: 2.4rem; }
  .cta-foot { margin-top: auto; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding-top: 2rem; }
  .cta-foot p { font-size: 1.1rem !important; color: var(--ink-soft) !important; margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .url { color: var(--accent) !important; font-weight: 700 !important; font-size: 1.4rem !important; }
  .handles { font-size: 1rem !important; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
</style>
